@startuml

title Email Reminder Sequence Diagram with Exceptions

actor User

participant "Frontend (Website)" as FE
participant "Apache\n(HTTP Server)" as Apache

box "Laravel Application" #LightGreen
  participant "Middleware" as MW
  participant "Controller" as C
  participant "Inventory Service" as Service
  participant "Messaging Service" as MessageService
  participant "Eloquent ORM" as ORM
end box

participant "Email Service SMTP" as Email
participant "Gmail" as Gmail
database "MariaDB Database" as DB

note left of DB
It is assumed the User is
authenticated/authorized unless an exception occurs.
end note

== Inventory Request Response ==

User -> FE: Submit borrow request form
activate User
activate FE
activate Apache
activate MW
activate C
activate Service
activate MessageService
activate Email
activate ORM
activate Gmail
activate DB

FE -> Apache: POST /borrowRequest


alt Route exists
    Apache -> MW: Forward HTTP request to Laravel middleware
   
else Route not found
    Apache --> FE: 404 Not Found

    FE --> User: Display "Borrow request route not found" error
    
    
end



alt Valid + Authorized
    MW -> C: Pass validated and authorized borrow request
    
else Validation/Auth error
    MW --> FE: 422 Unprocessable Entity / 401 Unauthorized / 403 Forbidden
    
    FE --> User: Display validation or authorization error
   
end



C -> Service: createBorrowRequest(requestData)


Service -> ORM: checkItemAvailability(itemId)

ORM -> DB: SELECT quantity_available FROM inventory_items WHERE item_id = ?


alt DB success
    DB --> ORM: Item availability result set
else DB failure
    DB --> ORM: SQL/database exception
   
    ORM --> Service: Availability lookup failed
    Service --> C: 500 Internal Server Error
    C --> FE: Return "Unable to verify item availability" error response
    FE --> User: Display system error: item availability could not be checked
  
end

ORM --> Service: Item availability status

alt Item available

    Service -> ORM: createBorrowRequestRecord(userId, itemId, requestedQuantity)
    ORM -> DB: INSERT INTO borrow_requests (...)

    alt Save success
        DB --> ORM: Insert successful
        ORM --> Service: Borrow request persisted

        Service --> C: Borrow request created successfully

        C -> Email: sendBorrowApprovalEmail(userEmail, requestDetails)

        alt Email success
            Email -> Gmail: Send approval notification email
            Gmail --> Email: Delivery accepted
            Email --> C: Approval email sent successfully
        else Email failure
            Email --> C: SMTP delivery failed for approval email
        end


    else Save failure
        DB --> ORM: Insert failed / SQL exception
        ORM --> Service: Borrow request persistence failed
        Service --> C: 500 Internal Server Error
    end

else Item unavailable

    Service --> C: Borrow request rejected due to insufficient stock

    C -> Email: sendBorrowRejectionEmail(userEmail, itemId, rejectionReason)

    alt Email success
        Email -> Gmail: Send rejection notification email
        Gmail --> Email: Delivery accepted
        Email --> C: Rejection email sent successfully
    else Email failure
        Email --> C: SMTP delivery failed for rejection email
    end


end


C --> FE: Return borrow request processing result

FE --> User: Display borrow request confirmation status



== Message Reminder Email ==

User -> FE: Open messages page


FE -> Apache: GET /messages


alt Route exists
    Apache -> MW: Forward HTTP request
else Route not found
    Apache --> FE: 404 Not Found

    FE --> User: Display "Messages route not found" error
   
end



alt Authorized
    MW -> C: Pass authenticated message page request
else Auth error
    MW --> FE: 401 Unauthorized / 403 Forbidden
    FE --> User: Display authentication or authorization error
  
end


C -> MessageService: checkMessageReminderTimeout(userId)

MessageService -> ORM: getLastUnreadMessageTimestamp(userId)
ORM -> DB: SELECT MAX(created_at) FROM messages WHERE recipient_id = ? AND is_read = 0

alt DB success
    DB --> ORM: Last unread message timestamp
else DB failure
    DB --> ORM: SQL/database exception
    ORM --> MessageService: Message timestamp lookup failed
    MessageService --> C: 500 Internal Server Error
    C --> FE: Return "Unable to check unread message timeout" error
    FE --> User: Display system error while checking message reminders
  
end

ORM --> MessageService: Timestamp lookup result

alt Timeout reached

    MessageService -> Email: sendUnreadMessageReminderEmail(userEmail, unreadMessageSummary)

    alt Email success
        Email -> Gmail: Send unread message reminder email
        Gmail --> Email: Delivery accepted
        Email --> MessageService: Reminder email sent successfully
    else Email failure
        Email --> MessageService: SMTP delivery failed for reminder email
    end


else No timeout
    note right of MessageService: No reminder email sent\nbecause timeout threshold was not reached
end


C --> FE: Return messages page response

FE --> User: Display message page status



== User Ban Notification ==

User -> FE: Submit login form


FE -> Apache: POST /login


alt Route exists
    Apache -> MW: Forward HTTP request
else Route not found
    Apache --> FE: 404 Not Found

    FE --> User: Display "Login route not found" error
    
end



alt Valid request
    MW -> C: Pass validated login credentials
else Validation error
    MW --> FE: 422 Unprocessable Entity
    FE --> User: Display login form validation error

end


C -> ORM: getUserByEmail(email)
ORM -> DB: SELECT id, email, banned_at, status FROM users WHERE email = ?

alt User exists
    DB --> ORM: User record returned with banned status
    ORM --> C: User lookup result

    C -> Email: sendUserBannedNotificationEmail(userEmail, banReason)

    alt Email success
        Email -> Gmail: Send banned account notification email
        Gmail --> Email: Delivery accepted
        Email --> C: Ban notification email sent successfully
    else Email failure
        Email --> C: SMTP delivery failed for ban notification
    end


    C --> FE: Return access denied response for banned user

else User not found
    DB --> ORM: Empty result set
    ORM --> C: User not found
    C --> FE: 404 User account not found

else DB failure
    DB --> ORM: SQL/database exception
    ORM --> C: User lookup failed
    C --> FE: 500 Internal Server Error
end


FE --> User: Display login or account status message
@enduml